Nigeria’s Minister of Communications and Digital Economy, Dr Isa Pantami, has urged state governors to key into the Federal government’s  National Digital Economy policy and strategy. President Muhammadu Buhari, on Nov. 29, 2019, unveiled the National Digital Economy Policy, initiated by the Federal Ministry of Communications and Digital Economy. As part of key requirements of the e-government master plan, the President has directed government institutions, “to create a digital transformation technical working group that will work with the Ministry of Communications and Digital Economy to ensure seamless and coordinated implementation of projects, programmes and policies